    {
      "id": "owasp",
      "label": "OWASP",
      "icon": "🛡️",
      "title_prefix": "OWASP Analysis",
      "default_tags": [
        "web",
        "security",
        "owasp"
      ],
      "variants": [
        {
          "id": "general",
          "label": "General",
          "title_prefix": "OWASP Top 10",
          "body_lines": [
            "## 🧪 OWASP Top 10 + WSTG Deep Dive",
            "",
            "### 🛡️ A01: Broken Access Control (WSTG-ATHZ)",
            "- [ ] **IDOR Check:** Change `user_id` or `UUID` in URLs/JSON. Try numeric increment/decrement.",
            "- [ ] **CORS Misconfig:** Check for `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` or `null`.",
            "- [ ] **Method Bypass:** Try `PUT` or `DELETE` on endpoints that only show `GET/POST`.",
            "- [ ] **Admin Panels:** Fuzz for `/admin`, `/config`, `/env`, `/_vti_bin`.",
            "",
            "### 🔐 A02: Cryptographic Failures (WSTG-CRYP)",
            "- [ ] **Sensitive Data in URL:** Check for tokens/PII in GET parameters (browser history leak).",
            "- [ ] **Weak TLS:** Use `testssl.sh`. Check for TLS 1.0/1.1 or Null Ciphers.",
            "- [ ] **HSTS:** Verify `Strict-Transport-Security` header is present.",
            "",
            "### 💉 A03: Injection (WSTG-INPV)",
            "- [ ] **SQLi:** Try `'`, `\"`, `1' OR 1=1--`, and Time-based payloads (`pg_sleep`).",
            "- [ ] **Second-Order:** Does a stored username payload execute when viewed in an admin dashboard?",
            "- [ ] **XSS:** Test `<script>alert(1)</script>` and `javascript:alert(1)` in `<a>` tags.",
            "- [ ] **NoSQL:** Check `{\"username\": {\"$ne\": \"\"}}` in JSON logins.",
            "- [ ] **SSTI:** Try `{{7*7}}` or `${7*7}` in template-heavy apps.",
            "",
            "### 🎨 A04: Insecure Design (WSTG-BUSL)",
            "- [ ] **Logic Bypass:** Can you skip a payment step by hitting the 'Success' URL directly?",
            "- [ ] **Race Conditions:** Use Burp Intruder to send 20+ concurrent 'Withdrawal' requests.",
            "- [ ] **Negative Values:** Try ordering `-1` items to see if the total price drops.",
            "",
            "### ⚙️ A05: Security Misconfiguration (WSTG-CONFIG)",
            "- [ ] **Subdomain Takeover:** Check for CNAMEs pointing to unclaimed S3/GitHub/Heroku buckets.",
            "- [ ] **Default Creds:** Check for `admin:admin`, `guest:guest`, `root:root`.",
            "- [ ] **Directory Listing:** Check if `/images/` or `/uploads/` shows a file index.",
            "- [ ] **Verbose Errors:** Trigger a 500 error; look for stack traces or DB versions.",
            "",
            "### 📦 A06: Vulnerable Components (WSTG-CONF)",
            "- [ ] **Header Inspection:** Check `X-Powered-By` or `Server` headers for old versions.",
            "- [ ] **JS Audit:** Run `retire.js` or check `Snyk` for outdated jQuery/Bootstrap.",
            "",
            "### 👤 A07: Auth Failures (WSTG-ATHN)",
            "- [ ] **Brute Force:** Check if the app locks you out after 5-10 failed attempts.",
            "- [ ] **Session Fixation:** Does the Cookie change after logging in?",
            "- [ ] **MFA Bypass:** Can you browse to `/dashboard` while the MFA prompt is active?",
            "",
            "### 🧩 A08: Data Integrity (WSTG-INPV)",
            "- [ ] **JWT Analysis:** Check for `\"alg\": \"none\"` or `kid` injection (pointing to /dev/null).",
            "- [ ] **Deserialization:** Look for base64 serialized objects in cookies (Java/PHP/Node).",
            "",
            "### 📊 A09: Logging/Monitoring (WSTG-LOGG)",
            "- [ ] **Log Injection:** Can you put `\\n` in a username to forge log entries?",
            "- [ ] **Audit Trail:** Are password changes and email updates logged?",
            "",
            "### 🌐 A10: SSRF (WSTG-INPV)",
            "- [ ] **Internal Metadata:** Try `http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/`.",
            "- [ ] **Localhost Scan:** Try `http://localhost:22` or `http://127.0.0.1:80`.",
            "",
            "---",
            "## 📝 Active Finding Summary",
            "| ID | WSTG | Impact | Status |",
            "|----|------|--------|--------|",
            "|    |      |        |        |",
            "",
            "## 📸 Proof of Concept",
            "**URL:** ",
            "**Payload:** ",
            "```http",
            "",
            "```"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "api",
          "label": "API Specific",
          "title_prefix": "OWASP API Security",
          "body_lines": [
            "## 🔌 OWASP API Security Top 10",
            "",
            "### 🔑 API1: Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA)",
            "- [ ] **ID Substitution:** Can you access `/api/v1/messages/{id}` of another user?",
            "- [ ] **Predictable IDs:** Are IDs sequential? Try incrementing to find other resources.",
            "",
            "### 🆔 API2: Broken Authentication",
            "- [ ] **Token Expiry:** Do JWTs or API keys expire properly?",
            "- [ ] **Unprotected Endpoints:** Do all endpoints require an `Authorization` header?",
            "",
            "### 📤 API3: Broken Object Property Level Authorization",
            "- [ ] **Mass Assignment:** Can you add `\"is_admin\": true` to a profile update JSON?",
            "- [ ] **Excessive Data Exposure:** Does the API return a full User object (including hashes) in the response?",
            "",
            "### 📉 API4: Unrestricted Resource Consumption",
            "- [ ] **Rate Limiting:** Can you send 1000 requests per minute without a 429 error?",
            "- [ ] **Pagination Stress:** Try `?limit=999999` to cause DoS or high memory usage.",
            "",
            "### 🧱 API5: Broken Function Level Authorization",
            "- [ ] **Admin Method on User Endpoint:** Try `DELETE` on a user resource as a normal user.",
            "- [ ] **Unauthorized Access:** Can a user access `/api/admin/stats`?",
            "",
            "### 🗺️ API6: Unrestricted Access to Business Logic",
            "- [ ] **Step Skipping:** Can you move from 'Cart' to 'Shipment' without 'Payment' via API calls?",
            "",
            "### 🛰️ API7: Server Side Request Forgery (SSRF)",
            "- [ ] **Webhooks:** If the API accepts a callback URL, try pointing it to internal IPs.",
            "",
            "### ⚙️ API8: Security Misconfiguration",
            "- [ ] **Method Enforcement:** Does the API reject non-standard methods (e.g., `HEAD`, `OPTIONS`)?",
            "- [ ] **Error Verbosity:** Does the API return stack traces in JSON responses?",
            "",
            "### 📦 API9: Improper Inventory Management",
            "- [ ] **Old Versions:** Is `/api/v1/` still active and unpatched compared to `/api/v2/`?",
            "- [ ] **Shadow APIs:** Are there undocumented endpoints like `/api/test` or `/api/debug`?",
            "",
            "### 🌪️ API10: Unsafe Consumption of APIs",
            "- [ ] **Third-party Trust:** Does the app trust data from integrated APIs without sanitization?",
            "",
            "---",
            "## 📝 API Findings Table",
            "| Endpoint | Method | Risk | Status |",
            "|----------|--------|------|--------|",
            "|          |        |      |        |"
          ]
        }
      ],
